description.narrative: (Tanzania): .<!--td {border: 1px solid #ccc;}br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}-->USAID Boresha Afya Southern will increase access to integrated, comprehensive, high-quality facility-based health services to address malaria, tuberculosis/multi-drug-resistant tuberculosis, family planning, and maternal, newborn, and child health in the regions of Njombe, Iringa, Morogoro, Mtwara, Lindi, and Ruvuma (malaria only). The award will provide grants to district governing authorities in order to promote integrated facility-based, patient-centered services that are harmonized and linked to demand-side interventions, facilitate joint planning and implementation with facilities and Council Health Management Teams, and assist with supervision, data review, and quality assurance with Regional HMTs. USAID Boresha Afya Southern will contribute to the U.S. government's objective of improving the health status of Tanzanians. the President's Malaria Initiative and Ending Preventable Child and Maternal Deaths initiatives. .
